# Project Structure & Import Boundaries

## Directory Ownership

| Directory | Owner | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `src/` | Anton (data/structure) + Sasha (visuals) | Frontend React SPA |
| `src/data/`, `src/types.ts` | Anton | Data loaders, TypeScript interfaces |
| `src/components/`, `src/styles/`, `src/hooks/` | Sasha | UI components, CSS, UI hooks |
| `parsers/` | Anton | Registry scrapers (80 parsers) |
| `workers/` | Anton | Background workers (quality, enrichment, verify) |
| `shared/` | Anton | Backend utilities (config, supabase, logger, types, guards) |

## Import Rules (HARD)

```
src/        → NEVER imports from parsers/, workers/, shared/
parsers/    → imports from parsers/core/ and shared/
workers/    → imports from shared/
shared/     → imports from npm packages only (no internal cross-imports)
```

Violation of these boundaries breaks the build and creates circular dependencies.

## File Naming

- Pages: `src/pages/XxxPage.tsx` (PascalCase + "Page" suffix)
- Components: `src/components/<category>/Xxx.tsx` (PascalCase)
- Hooks: `src/hooks/useXxx.ts` (camelCase, "use" prefix)
- Tests: colocated `*.test.{ts,tsx}`
- Parsers: `parsers/registries/<cc>-<regulator>.ts` (lowercase country code + regulator abbreviation)
- Workers: `workers/<name>/run.ts` (lowercase, run.ts as entry)

## Key Constraints

- NO: MUI, Tailwind, Lenis, jQuery, react-simple-maps
- CSS: Bootstrap 5.3 + custom `.st-*` classes + GSAP
- Cards: always `.clip-lg` class
- Icons: Lucide React only
- Map: MapLibre GL JS only
- Charts: Recharts only
- Stride data source: CONFIDENTIAL — never mention in public code/docs/commits
